      • power

        public java.math.BigDecimal power(java.math.BigDecimal a,
                         java.math.BigDecimal b)
        Description copied from interface: Evaluator
        Returns a BigDecimal whose value is a.pow(b), The power is computed exactly, to unlimited precision.

        The parameter n must be in the range 0 through 999999999, inclusive. ZERO.pow(0) returns ONE. Note that future releases may expand the allowable exponent range of this method.

        Parameters: n - power to raise this BigDecimal to.

        Specified by:
        power in interface Evaluator
        Parameters:
        a - Left side of expression, value that should be raised
        b - Right side of expression, value that should used to raise by
        Returns:
        a.pow(b) using the ANSI standard X3.274-1996 algorithm

        See Also:
        BigDecimal.pow(int)

      • root

        public java.math.BigDecimal root(java.math.BigDecimal a)
        Description copied from interface: Evaluator
        Returns the correctly rounded positive square root of a double value. Special cases: If the argument is NaN or less than zero, then the result is NaN. If the argument is positive infinity, then the result is positive infinity. If the argument is positive zero or negative zero, then the result is the same as the argument. Otherwise, the result is the double value closest to the true mathematical square root of the argument value.
        Specified by:
        root in interface Evaluator
        Parameters:
        a - value which square root should be computed
        Returns:
        the positive square root of a. If the argument is NaN or less than zero, the result is NaN.
